# JSR Release

- Keep every publishable member on lockstep `0.0.1-alpha.0` until the release program advances it;
  see `docs/architecture/STANDARDS.md`.
- Each package `deno.json` needs JSR audit metadata, explicit exports, and explicit publish
  include/exclude lists as described in `docs/architecture/STANDARDS.md`.
- `deno publish --dry-run --allow-dirty` is the release-resolution gate; slow-type cleanup is a
  package remediation task, not a reason to weaken metadata.
- Public docs and examples are part of the package contract; keep examples compiling and avoid
  private workspace paths in published surfaces.
- Use `.agents/skills/jsr-audit/SKILL.md` for JSR readiness reviews.
